55.1	Abrahamic_religion	Abrahamic religions	Abrahamic religions are the monotheistic faiths emphasizing and tracing their common origin to Abraham or recognizing a spiritual tradition identified with him. They are one of the three major divisions in comparative religion, along with Indian religions (Dharmic) and East Asian religions (Taoic). As of the early twenty-first century , it was estimated that 54% of the world's population (3.8 billion people) considered themselves adherents of the Abrahamic religions, about 30% of other religions, and 16% of no religion.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/ReligionSymbolAbr.PNG/220px-ReligionSymbolAbr.PNG
